==English==
===Etymology===
German acronym of '''''Fl'''ieger'''a'''bwehr'''k'''anone''. First attested [[w:1940|1940]] as ''an anti-aircraft gun''. Sense of ''adverse criticism'' attested since [[w:1963|1963]] in [[American English]]. 
===Noun===
#Ground-based anti-aircraft guns firing explosive shells.
#Anti-aircraft shell fire.
#(''figurative, informal'') Adverse criticism.
#(''informal'') Public relations spokesperson. Also spelt [[flack]].